 <H1>Lossless Join Decompositions</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Decomposition of R into X and Y is lossless-join w.r.t. a set of FDs F if, for every instance r that satisfies F:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>          (r)              (r)   =  r
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>It is always true that   r            (r)             (r)
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>In general, the other direction does not hold!  If it does, the decomposition is lossless-join. 
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Definition extended to decomposition into 3 or more relations in a straightforward way.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>It is essential that all decompositions used to deal with redundancy be lossless!  (Avoids Problem (2).) </H2>
</UL></P>
